org.rlcommunity.rlviz.dynamicloading
Class LocalJarAgentEnvironmentLoader

java.lang.Object
  org.rlcommunity.rlviz.dynamicloading.LocalJarAgentEnvironmentLoader
All Implemented Interfaces:
DynamicLoaderInterface
Direct Known Subclasses:
LocalJarAgentLoader, LocalJarEnvironmentLoader
public class LocalJarAgentEnvironmentLoader
extends java.lang.Object
implements DynamicLoaderInterface

My belief is that our classes are leaking like crazy because we are forever loading them using new classloaders and a bunch of the statically allocated stuff is just hanging around. I want to cache loaded classes so we only load them a single time.

Author:
btanner
